plugins.name: Mode Match
plugins.description:
Mode Match lets you take a variable's value from one mode and apply it to other modes. Match a single variable, group of variables, or all variables in a collection!


  1. Select your multi-mode collection
  2. Select the source mode (copy from)
  3. Select the destination mode (copy to)
  4. Enter the path to a group of variables or a single variable (see below for bulk actions)
  5. Update ✨


Tip

  1. Keep your variable window open to see the changes.
  2. Use the Refresh button to pull in changes to the variables made when the plugin window is open. (see below for copy & paste)
  3. Use clear to quickly delete the path.


Bulk Actions

You will most likely want to run this on a group or the entire collection:

  1. Update all variables within a group by entering a path/to/group
  2. Update all variables in the collection by entering / @all or @root in the path input


Plugin Notes

  1. Collection list will only show collections with more than 1 mode
  2. Variable names and paths are case sensitive
  3. Updating variables, especially those linked to text styles may take longer to propagate


Supports

  1. All variable types (number, string, boolean, color)
  2. Aliasing
  3. Raw values


Copy/Paste Figma Bug

If you copy/paste variables between collections, you may need to reload the tab in order for those variables to register in their new collection.

accepted.name: Murph
accepted.description: Systems Designer • Plugin Author • Rectangle Lover

plugins.tagline: Match variable values across modes.

plugins.name: QuickToken
plugins.description:
QuickToken is the Figma plugin that enables instant variable import and seamless organization. Designed for designers who prioritize efficiency, QuickToken allows you to quickly insert variables into Figma’s local variables as design tokens. It supports collections and groups, keeping all variables clear and organized. Simplify your variable management and speed up your workflow with this powerful, efficient plugin!


Supported name schemes:


Create Variable Collection

#Collection


Create Variable Group

Group/


Create Variable

variable-name: value


The variable type recognition is automatically

based on the variable value itself.


Supported variable types


  1. Float 30
  2. Colors #333, #334455, rgb(0,100,100), rgba(2,2,2,0.1)
  3. Boolean: true, false
  4. String: 'Hello'
  5. Variable link: var(variable-name)

plugins.name: iMessage AI Chat Builder
plugins.description:
Accelerate your design workflow with an AI-powered plugin that integrates seamlessly with the iMessage Chat Builder UI kit. Use this plugin to instantly generate realistic iMessage screens and prototypes.


Using this plugin will allow you to configure the following chat properties:

  1. The number of chat participants
  2. The maximum number of messages in the chat
  3. Whether iMessage should default to light or dark mode
  4. The conversation topic and tone


Getting Started

To get started, follow these quick steps:


1. Install required fonts and symbols

This plugin uses Apple’s SF Pro and SF Mono font families - in addition to SF Symbols.


These fonts are not bundled with this file. SF Pro should now work natively within Figma’s desktop client, but you’ll still need to download and install SF Mono manually if you haven’t already done so.


2. Generate and enter an Anthropic API key

To use the plugin - you’ll need an Anthropic API key.


You can get one by:

  1. Visiting the Anthropic Console
  2. Signing in or creating an account
  3. Navigating to the API Key section of your account settings
  4. Clicking ‘Create Key’


Paste that API key into the plugin when prompted. Your key is stored locally and never shared.


Note: Anthropic may charge for API usage. Review Anthropic’s API pricing before proceeding with plugin use.


---


This plugin is not affiliated with or endorsed by Apple Inc, Figma Inc, or Anthropic PBC.

accepted.name: Pat Dugan
accepted.description: Front front, back back, sucker grab a snack pack.

plugins.tagline: Create convincing iMessage prototypes using AI. Turn ideas into iMessage prototypes instantly.

plugins.name: Font Detective
plugins.description:
Ever need to know exactly which fonts are in your project without clicking through dozens of text layers? Manually checking for fonts is slow and easy to miss one, especially in complex files.


Font Detective instantly scans your selection and provides a clean list of every font family it finds.


No more guesswork, no more hunting. ✨


How it works:


  1. Select a frame - Click on a single frame or select multiple frames
  2. Run "Font Detective" - One click and you're done
  3. Get results - Immediately see a complete list of all font families spotted within your selection. It's that simple!


Key Benefits:


  1. Quick Typography Audits - Get a fast and accurate inventory of the fonts in any file or component
  2. Maintain Consistency - Easily spot unwanted fonts that don't belong in your design system
  3. Streamline Cleanup - Use the generated list as a checklist to consolidate your font styles
  4. Effortless Handoff - Quickly provide a list of all used fonts to developers or teammates
  5. Simple & Fast - No complex settings. Just select and run for instant results


Perfect for designers, design teams, and anyone working with typography in Figma! 🎨


Feedback is welcome!

accepted.name: Lorenzo Brandimarte
accepted.description: Web and UI Designer | No-code developer

plugins.tagline: Font Detective scans your frame and provides a clean list of every font family it finds.

plugins.name: Screen Counter
plugins.description:
Tired of manually counting screens in your Figma file? Meet Screen Counter, your new best friend for quick and intelligent screen counting!


✨ Here’s what it can do:

  1. Count selected screens in just a click – no more eye strain or second guessing.
  2. Add prefixes (like login, home, product) to group screens with similar flows or purposes.
  3. If multiple screens share the same prefix, we’ll count them as 1 (because duh, they’re basically twins).
  4. If you don’t add a prefix, we’ll count each screen individually, as they should be!


Simple, clear, and a little smarter than your average screen counter.


🖱️ Select → Prefix → Count → Done.


Try it now and turn screen chaos into clean counts!
plugins.tagline: Count Smarter, Not Harder!

plugins.name: OxyReIcon
plugins.description:
OxyReIcon is the ultimate Figma plugin for designers and icon creators who want to streamline their workflow and create consistent, professional-looking icon sets effortlessly.


Key Features:

  1. Instantly create frames around your vector icons
  2. Customize background and icon colors with opacity control
  3. Automatically align icons in a customizable grid layout
  4. Resize icons and frames with precise control
  5. Convert framed icons back to vectors with a single click
  6. Save and load your preferred settings for quick access


Whether you're creating a comprehensive icon library, designing a cohesive UI, or preparing assets for development handoff, OxyReIcon has got you covered. Say goodbye to manual resizing and positioning – let our plugin do the heavy lifting so you can focus on what matters most: designing great icons.
plugins.tagline: Transform your vector icons into perfectly styled, grid-aligned frames in seconds.

plugins.name: snapInsert
plugins.description:
snapInsert is a powerful Figma plugin designed to streamline the process of searching filtering and adding component instances into your designs.

Perfect for designers and teams who work with large design systems, Component Filter helps you save time and maintain focus on your design tasks.


Key Features:

• Component Set Filtering: Easily filter components by their set names to focus on specific groups within your design system.

• Dynamic Key-Value Filtering: Use key-value pairs to narrow down your search and find exactly what you need based on component properties like size, orientation, or any custom attributes.

• Real-Time Results: As you apply filters, see immediate updates to the component list, ensuring you always have the most relevant components in view.

• Intuitive UI: The plugin features a clean, user-friendly interface that integrates seamlessly with Figma, making it easy to apply filters and manage your components.


Note:

Currently, Component Filter only searches for components within the file you are working on. In future releases, users will be able to search components from published design libraries, expanding the plugin's functionality to cover broader design systems.
plugins.tagline: Effortlessly search and insert component instances from sets or singles into your designs.
